crossdevice_def:
A "user searching for information [..] on his desktop before continuing the task on his mobile device. Better support for task continuation could help the user resume his restaurant search when mobile. Such contiguous cross-device tasks [are] those resumed soon on the post-switch device.";
"a cross-device search is defined by a 7-tuple, including the personal search history, the pre-switch and post-switch queries, the pre-switch and post-switch sessions, and the devices used before and after the switch.";
cross-device search; multi-device usage
